for-each loop in java

[for-each loop in java](https://www.flowerbrackets.com/for-each-loop-in-java/)

for-each in java traverse each element of an array sequentially without using index or counter. for-each loop or enhanced for loop was introduced in JDK 1.5 Hereâ€™s the syntax and example on for each loop.

Syntax:

for(<DataType of array><variablename> : <Array to be iterated>)
{
   // code
}


example of for each loop in java

import java.util.*;
public class ForEachLoopExample
{
   public static void main(String[] args)
   {
      int[] numbers = {2, 4, 6, 8, 10};
      // for each loop
      for(int n : numbers)
      {
         System.out.println(n);
      }
   }
}
